{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"459e513d-ccb9-4a77-892b-4fc57248f54a","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nYour `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required (it builds the test project as an executable MTP host). Just drop the other property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_jp7DeZxcbEjPTlR5V9ShvD","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_QKpAaT9HCN1sBzpYBaVJLr","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-358191291c564c18b8288ceac59bbd87/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":""},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-358191291c564c18b8288ceac59bbd87/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"54f49a61-16ec-4e00-8ca6-6bd8b2e800c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. \n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt into MTP support with `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10 it's no longer needed because MTP is the default.\n\nLet me provide the guidance and make the change.","outputTokens":420},"id":"545be4c1-4ad3-4b24-aa4d-85f87b7b3927","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:54:08.217Z","parentId":"4516491a-b3c1-4037-9e72-dcf064d94594"}
